SIMPLE: moisten
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moisten
<hw>Mois"ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Moistened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Moistening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
damp; to wet in a small degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A pipe a little <qex>moistened</qex> on the inside.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To soften by making moist; to make tender.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It <qex>moistened</qex> not his executioner's heart with any
pity.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moistener</ent>⟦br⟧
